description:
Hey HN! Christine and Steven here. As a PM and engineer, we’ve both evaluated and purchased a lot of software. One of the biggest frustrations was figuring out how much it would cost us without having to go through the sales process. When we did have a quote, we had no idea if we were getting a good deal or ripped off.

We built a site where you can see what other companies are actually paying for SaaS and enterprise software. Buyers contribute prices via quotes, pricing proposals, and other documentation to ensure quality.

We unlocked Talkdesk for Show HN users so that you can use the product without needing to sign in or upgrade. Check it out at https://www.pricelevel.com/showhn. Would love to hear any feedback, thank you!

Comments URL: https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=39980222

description:
The Chronicle of Philanthropy has been the premier source of news, information, analysis, and opinion in the social impact space since its founding in 1988. Each year, nearly 350,000 nonprofit professionals, foundation executives, board members, fundraisers, donors, and others working to advance the common good rely on the Chronicle’s indispensable information and practical advice.

In Spring 2023, the Chronicle became a fully-independent 501c3 nonprofit organization. In the coming months, we will be expanding our team rapidly. We intend to hire talented journalists from diverse backgrounds to help us respond to the stories and needs of a rapidly evolving sector. We’ll also be building a strong team of media business professionals and operational experts to help us create a financially sustainable, impact-focused organization. We believe that creating a diverse, equitable, and inclusive team made up of individuals with varied life experiences and perspectives is essential
title: The Chronicle of Philanthropy
